    "Due to the nature of b lang as a t-test value, a small value of b lang that is lower than the significance threshold indicates the existence of bias.",
    "Following the bias aspects in social science that are discussed in Section 2.2, we establish 3 aspects to measure biases in language style: (1) Language Formality, (2) Language Positivity, and",
    "(3) Language Agency.",
    "Biases in Language Formality Our method uses language formality as a proxy to reflect the level of language professionalism.",
    "We define biases in Language Formality to be statistically significant differences in the percentage of formal sentences in male and female-generated documents."
